1
00:00:08,578 --> 00:00:18,592
♪

2
00:00:18,625 --> 00:00:28,674
♪

3
00:00:28,674 --> 00:00:38,688
♪

4
00:01:38,039 --> 00:01:45,616
♪

5
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:54,696
{\an8}<i>(Sasori)</i>
<i>Over there?</i>

6
00:01:54,728 --> 00:01:55,664
{\an1}<i>(Itachi)</i>
<i>Yeah...</i>

7
00:01:57,065 --> 00:01:58,934
The "Akatsuki"?!

8
00:01:58,968 --> 00:02:02,740
{\an1}Don't know and don't care! Now
get lost! You're keeping me from
my "art appreciation"  time.

9
00:02:02,773 --> 00:02:07,180
{\an1}And I have to take this
brat on as my partner?

10
00:02:07,213 --> 00:02:14,055
{\an1}Sure, he's full of
energy, but he seems like
the early death type.

11
00:02:14,090 --> 00:02:16,293
{\an1}It's our Leader's orders.

12
00:02:16,326 --> 00:02:18,730
{\an1}His talent will be very useful.

13
00:02:18,762 --> 00:02:21,766
{\an1}You know about my
talent?! But how?!

14
00:02:21,799 --> 00:02:23,370
{\an1}Who are you? Talk!

15
00:02:23,403 --> 00:02:28,310
{\an5}(Kisame)
We know you're aiding
anti-government factions
with terrorist bombings.

16
00:02:28,343 --> 00:02:32,815
{\an1}And we are also aware that
you're a rogue ninja...

17
00:02:32,849 --> 00:02:35,953
{\an1}...So just what exactly
is your purpose?

18
00:02:35,986 --> 00:02:38,324
(Deidara)
Purpose?! I don't
need a purpose!

19
00:02:38,357 --> 00:02:44,232
{\an1}I take commissions to make
explosions... using my art!

20
00:02:44,265 --> 00:02:46,135
Disgusting.

21
00:02:46,168 --> 00:02:48,405
Is he finished?

22
00:02:48,438 --> 00:02:52,910
{\an1}Who knows... Who cares...

23
00:02:52,943 --> 00:02:55,214
{\an1}I'll handle this...

24
00:02:58,919 --> 00:03:01,222
{\an1}[metal scratching metal]

25
00:03:05,027 --> 00:03:09,834
{\an1}To be clear... I'm still not
going to stop in the pursuit of
my art!

26
00:03:09,867 --> 00:03:12,137
{\an1}As you please...

27
00:03:12,172 --> 00:03:18,681
{\an1}But... You're part of
the Akatsuki. You will
fulfill your missions.

28
00:03:27,794 --> 00:03:30,964
{\an1}Yeah, all right.  I understand.

29
00:03:30,997 --> 00:03:35,971
{\an1}But you...! Don't ever try
to catch me in a genjutsu
again! Hmph!

30
00:03:36,004 --> 00:03:40,177
{\an1}You're one of us now.  I doubt
that I'll have to use it on you.

31
00:03:40,211 --> 00:03:45,486
{\an1}Well, good! But just remember,
I wouldn't mind giving you a
taste of my art!

32
00:03:45,519 --> 00:03:47,054
{\an1}Leave it at that.

33
00:03:47,087 --> 00:03:48,723
<i>(Tendo Pain)</i>
<i>Sasori...</i>

34
00:03:48,757 --> 00:03:49,692
{\an1}Hm?

35
00:03:49,725 --> 00:03:53,129
{\an1}Partner with Deidara and
go kill Orochimaru.

36
00:03:53,162 --> 00:03:55,332
About time...

37
00:03:55,366 --> 00:03:58,270
Hold on! Who is
this Orochimaru?

38
00:03:58,303 --> 00:04:00,507
{\an1}I'll tell you on the way.

39
00:04:00,540 --> 00:04:04,211
{\an1}We believe that Orochimaru has
escaped into the Land of Wind.

40
00:04:04,245 --> 00:04:06,948
{\an1}But beyond that, we don't
really know anything.

41
00:04:06,982 --> 00:04:09,352
{\an1}That's all I need to know...

42
00:04:09,385 --> 00:04:10,888
...Let's go.

43
00:04:10,921 --> 00:04:11,989
{\an3}Hmph.

44
00:04:12,022 --> 00:04:15,026
Boy, you Akatsuki guys
sure like to bark orders!

45
00:04:15,059 --> 00:04:16,495
<i>(Sasori)</i>
<i>Just hurry up...</i>

46
00:04:16,529 --> 00:04:18,064
Yeah, I'm coming!

47
00:04:19,434 --> 00:04:22,471
<i>(Tendo Pain)</i>
<i>Itachi and Kisame, the</i>
<i>Hidden Grass Village.</i>

48
00:04:25,475 --> 00:04:27,278
What about my partner?

49
00:04:27,311 --> 00:04:29,213
{\an1}Wait a bit longer...

50
00:04:31,349 --> 00:04:34,253
{\an1}<i>(Sasori)</i>
<i>I've ordered Kabuto</i>
<i>to keep me updated.</i>

51
00:04:34,287 --> 00:04:37,057
{\an1}<i> He has several methods</i>
<i>at his disposal. </i>

52
00:04:37,090 --> 00:04:41,163
{\an1}If they're headed to the Land
of Wind, this is the spot...

53
00:04:48,608 --> 00:04:50,276
[gasp]

54
00:04:55,317 --> 00:04:59,156
{\an1}The Great Sand Dune
of the East...

55
00:04:59,189 --> 00:05:03,161
{\an1}I see. That's one place
the villagers won't go.

56
00:05:03,194 --> 00:05:05,832
Is that where
you're from, my man?

57
00:05:05,866 --> 00:05:08,235
{\an1}Never mind that.

58
00:05:08,268 --> 00:05:11,273
{\an1}Anyway, that location
works out perfectly.

59
00:05:13,008 --> 00:05:17,281
{\an8}<i>[howling wind]</i>

60
00:05:17,314 --> 00:05:18,583
{\an1}That's his hideout.

61
00:05:18,617 --> 00:05:21,120
{\an1}You can leave it to my art!

62
00:05:21,153 --> 00:05:23,457
{\an1}I'll just blow the
entire thing up!

63
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:26,594
{\an1}We don't even know if
he's there or not!

64
00:05:26,628 --> 00:05:28,330
{\an1}[quick gasp]

65
00:05:32,503 --> 00:05:33,104
[hiss]

66
00:05:33,137 --> 00:05:34,506
Sand Snakes!

67
00:05:34,540 --> 00:05:36,308
{\an1}<i>(Sasori)</i>
<i>It's useless...</i>

68
00:05:36,341 --> 00:05:39,345
{\an1}<i>...He already knows we're here.</i>

69
00:05:39,379 --> 00:05:40,648
Seriously?

70
00:05:40,681 --> 00:05:42,017
{\an1}Let's go.

71
00:05:49,928 --> 00:05:53,599
{\an1}I was under the impression that
Itachi would be the one to come,

72
00:05:53,633 --> 00:05:57,171
{\an1}but apparently the Akatsuki has
sent you two instead?

73
00:05:57,204 --> 00:05:59,908
{\an1}We'll kill you without
hesitation, traitor.

74
00:05:59,942 --> 00:06:02,278
{\an1}You think you can?

75
00:06:02,312 --> 00:06:05,149
{\an1}You're the Hidden
Stone boy, right?

76
00:06:05,182 --> 00:06:06,484
{\an1}From the Demolitions Unit?

77
00:06:06,518 --> 00:06:09,120
{\an1}I'm not a kid! So don't
treat me like one!

78
00:06:13,226 --> 00:06:17,099
{\an1}Keep watch from above and
make sure he doesn't escape.

79
00:06:17,132 --> 00:06:20,972
{\an1}What gives, my man? You
want to capture him
yourself or something?

80
00:06:21,005 --> 00:06:25,612
{\an1}Yeah, since you have no
grudges against him, right?

81
00:06:25,645 --> 00:06:27,213
[annoyed grunt]

82
00:06:28,749 --> 00:06:31,086
{\an1}Well if you want back-up, just
call on me, all right?

83
00:06:31,118 --> 00:06:32,187
Hmph!

84
00:06:34,290 --> 00:06:38,529
{\an1}I have the
geographical advantage.

85
00:06:45,706 --> 00:06:47,676
{\an1}So that's your art, huh?

86
00:06:48,677 --> 00:06:52,483
{\an1}You're aware of the Third
Kazekage's power, aren't you?

87
00:06:52,516 --> 00:06:54,251
Yes.

88
00:06:54,284 --> 00:06:59,191
{\an1}My hobby is to collect things
that I find interesting,  so I
took a little something...

89
00:07:09,774 --> 00:07:11,342
{\an1}What the hell...!?

90
00:07:11,375 --> 00:07:14,013
{\an1}Huh...? What is that?

91
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:27,298
It's you Sasori How
dare you do this to me!

92
00:07:27,565 --> 00:07:30,269
{\an1}What is this, you damn snake?

93
00:07:30,302 --> 00:07:33,474
{\an1}The Third Kazekage,
whom you killed.

94
00:07:33,507 --> 00:07:36,344
{\an1}I used a Forbidden Jutsu to
resurrect him.

95
00:07:36,378 --> 00:07:39,549
The outcome here will be
different than last time...

96
00:07:39,582 --> 00:07:41,719
{\an1}Enough of your complaints...

97
00:07:45,825 --> 00:07:48,061
Now, then

98
00:07:48,095 --> 00:07:52,300
{\an1}<i>...Your Human Puppet against</i>
<i>my Forbidden Jutsu.</i>

99
00:07:52,333 --> 00:07:55,438
{\an1}Let's see which is best!

100
00:07:56,339 --> 00:07:57,507
{\an1}Damn you...

101
00:07:57,540 --> 00:08:02,648
{\an1}Iron Sand: Scattered Showers!

102
00:08:10,426 --> 00:08:13,430
[shouting]

103
00:08:20,273 --> 00:08:24,179
{\an1}That puppet stops working when
Sand hits it, doesn't it?

104
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:27,617
{\an1}Don't you dare lecture
me about puppets!

105
00:08:28,886 --> 00:08:31,388
{\an1}<i>[fast whirring sound]</i>

106
00:08:33,324 --> 00:08:34,393
[grunt]

107
00:08:42,571 --> 00:08:48,379
{\an1}Unlike the real thing, I've
built lots of hidden tricks
into this puppet.

108
00:08:48,412 --> 00:08:50,549
{\an1}Now it's your turn...

109
00:08:50,582 --> 00:08:53,253
Not yet...

110
00:08:54,588 --> 00:08:55,757
What...?!

111
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:58,359
{\an1}This is a form of immortality.

112
00:08:58,393 --> 00:09:01,565
{\an1}It can't die since
it's already dead.

113
00:09:01,598 --> 00:09:03,467
{\an1}We'll just see about that!

114
00:09:12,546 --> 00:09:14,317
[gasp]

115
00:09:16,819 --> 00:09:17,888
[gasp]

116
00:09:22,228 --> 00:09:23,762
Hiya!

117
00:09:23,964 --> 00:09:27,768
[explosions]

118
00:09:27,802 --> 00:09:31,908
{\an1}Well, then? How'd
you like my art?

119
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:42,756
{\an1}Why won't it die?!

120
00:09:42,789 --> 00:09:48,231
{\an1}After you both die, I'm going to
resurrect you in the same way.

121
00:09:50,734 --> 00:09:56,743
{\an1}Although, to be honest,
what I really wanted was to
get hold of Itachi's body.

122
00:10:01,850 --> 00:10:06,323
My man! Does that guy
have a weakness?!

123
00:10:06,356 --> 00:10:09,727
{\an1}Resurrection isn't one
of the Third's abilities

124
00:10:09,761 --> 00:10:11,397
{\an1}[grunt]

125
00:10:15,803 --> 00:10:19,841
{\an1}You're going to become
my pawns forever!

126
00:10:24,481 --> 00:10:26,419
{\an1}<i>(Third Kazekage)</i>
<i>Stop kidding around.</i>

127
00:10:26,451 --> 00:10:27,353
{\an3}[gasp]

128
00:10:27,386 --> 00:10:31,525
{\an1}Don't forget... that I
am the Third Kazekage!

129
00:10:31,558 --> 00:10:37,434
{\an1}...I am not your pawn!

130
00:10:43,675 --> 00:10:48,882
{\an1}Oh, my I wonder if my jutsu
wasn't complete...

131
00:10:49,884 --> 00:10:51,052
Take this!

132
00:10:55,859 --> 00:10:56,995
{\an1}Did that get him?

133
00:10:59,965 --> 00:11:03,803
Hey, no running!

134
00:11:08,043 --> 00:11:10,713
Hiya!

135
00:11:15,553 --> 00:11:17,491
Ha! My art!

136
00:11:18,657 --> 00:11:21,029
{\an1}is an explosion!

137
00:11:21,062 --> 00:11:24,467
{\an1}Hey, c'mon now...

138
00:11:28,538 --> 00:11:33,379
{\an5}(Sasori)
We searched the whole mountain
of rubble but didn't find his
corpse...

139
00:11:33,413 --> 00:11:36,116
{\an1}...So we can't say for
sure that we killed him.

140
00:11:36,150 --> 00:11:39,854
{\an1}(Deidara)
If he's still alive, I swear
I'll kill him myself.

141
00:11:39,888 --> 00:11:43,494
{\an1}...And what's with that
ridiculous jutsu, anyway?!

142
00:11:43,528 --> 00:11:46,798
(Tendo Pain)
Do you know about it?

143
00:11:46,831 --> 00:11:50,503
{\an1}It's probably the Second
Hokage's Reanimation Jutsu.

144
00:11:50,537 --> 00:11:55,410
{\an1}It brings the dead back to life
and allows one to control them
like puppets.

145
00:11:55,444 --> 00:11:57,980
{\an1}You can't kill them
even if you try.

146
00:11:58,014 --> 00:12:01,886
{\an5}(Itachi)
You have to use a Sealing Jutsu
or suppress their movement
through force.

147
00:12:02,220 --> 00:12:05,124
{\an1}(Deidara)
Or just kill Orochimaru, right?

148
00:12:05,157 --> 00:12:07,994
(Itachi)
Even that won't stop a
Reanimation...

149
00:12:08,463 --> 00:12:09,997
{\an1}(Deidara)
What do you mean?

150
00:12:10,031 --> 00:12:13,068
(Tendo Pain)
Be wary of Orochimaru
from now on.

151
00:12:13,102 --> 00:12:16,173
{\an1}If he's alive, he's bound
to make another move.

152
00:12:16,207 --> 00:12:20,712
{\an4}(Deidara)
It would be really out of the
ordinary if he survived <i>that</i>
explosion, hmph!

153
00:12:20,745 --> 00:12:24,952
(Sasori)
No one who joins us is
"ordinary."

154
00:12:24,985 --> 00:12:27,922
(Konan)
It sounds like we have another
immortal on our hands now.

155
00:12:27,956 --> 00:12:34,198
{\an5}(Tendo Pain)
The Land of Steam has requested
that we eliminate a homicidal
maniac that's appeared.

156
00:12:34,232 --> 00:12:37,236
{\an1}(Kakuzu)
Don't they have their own
Hidden Steam shinobi?

157
00:12:37,269 --> 00:12:40,141
(Konan)
Apparently, they can't kill him.

158
00:12:40,174 --> 00:12:42,511
(Itachi)
So this maniac is immortal, too?

159
00:12:42,544 --> 00:12:45,548
{\an4}(Deidara)
Was he also
"reani-whatevered"
by Orochimaru?

160
00:12:45,581 --> 00:12:49,786
(Tendo Pain)
I'm dispatching a different
team this time.

161
00:12:51,990 --> 00:12:54,793
{\an8}<i>[birds chirping]</i>

162
00:13:00,035 --> 00:13:01,538
[gasp]

163
00:13:01,737 --> 00:13:04,942
{\an1}(Hidan)
You, there

164
00:13:04,975 --> 00:13:09,080
{\an1}[chuckle] Would you like
to join the Way of Jashin?

165
00:13:10,983 --> 00:13:15,256
{\an8}<i>[bird noises]</i>

166
00:13:15,290 --> 00:13:18,794
This wasn't for money
or revenge.

167
00:13:18,827 --> 00:13:22,099
This was done out of a
deep desire to kill.

168
00:13:22,133 --> 00:13:26,004
{\an1}There are many other ways to
quench a thirst for blood...

169
00:13:26,038 --> 00:13:28,708
{\an1}I believe he had some
other purpose in mind.

170
00:13:28,741 --> 00:13:33,081
You really have a way of
irritating me, you know that?

171
00:13:35,117 --> 00:13:40,326
{\an1}And you...  did you come to make
sure I don't kill Itachi?

172
00:13:40,359 --> 00:13:43,897
{\an1}There are no other Sensory
types besides me. Plus

173
00:13:43,930 --> 00:13:47,969
{\an1}I'm certain that none of the
others are cut out to be
decoys...

174
00:13:48,002 --> 00:13:50,906
{\an1}Decoys?

175
00:13:56,848 --> 00:13:59,018
[grunt]

176
00:14:02,155 --> 00:14:04,727
<i>(Hidan)</i>
<i>Hey!  You there!</i>

177
00:14:04,759 --> 00:14:07,664
{\an1}Would you like to join
the Way of Jashin?

178
00:14:07,697 --> 00:14:08,932
Way of Jashin?

179
00:14:08,965 --> 00:14:11,603
{\an1}Yeah, that's right! The
Way of Jashin...

180
00:14:11,637 --> 00:14:13,905
{\an1}And what exactly is that?

181
00:14:13,939 --> 00:14:17,810
{\an1}It's an ideology where you can
kill people and you won't be
punished at all.

182
00:14:17,844 --> 00:14:20,815
{\an1}In fact, it pleases Lord Jashin
even more if you do just that!

183
00:14:20,849 --> 00:14:22,218
{\an3}Oh

184
00:14:22,251 --> 00:14:25,055
It's a wonderful
teaching, isn't it?

185
00:14:25,088 --> 00:14:27,158
{\an1}What do you say, wanna join up?

186
00:14:27,191 --> 00:14:31,163
{\an1}Ah. So you clearly must be that
homicidal maniac that we heard
about...

187
00:14:31,196 --> 00:14:33,734
{\an1}What?  A maniac? No, at all!

188
00:14:33,768 --> 00:14:37,372
{\an1}Look, I'm simply offering up
prayers to Lord Jashin.

189
00:14:37,406 --> 00:14:41,712
{\an1}And now it seems like I'm gonna
have to offer you up, as well!

190
00:14:42,079 --> 00:14:43,981
Your thoughts?

191
00:14:44,014 --> 00:14:46,252
He doesn't seem to
be a Reanimation.

192
00:14:46,285 --> 00:14:49,723
{\an1}Fine. I'll test him to
see how immortal he is.

193
00:14:49,757 --> 00:14:53,861
{\an1}Who are you guys?  And why are
you all dressed the same way?

194
00:14:53,895 --> 00:14:55,097
{\an1}What, are you in a band?

195
00:14:55,130 --> 00:14:58,269
{\an1}Let's see...  The gloomy one
over there plays bass guitar

196
00:14:58,302 --> 00:15:00,871
{\an1}The girl does vocals
and keyboards...

197
00:15:00,905 --> 00:15:04,944
{\an1}No, wait, the emo guy's got
be handling the vocals...

198
00:15:04,977 --> 00:15:06,815
{\an1}We're nothing like that.

199
00:15:06,847 --> 00:15:10,753
{\an1}I still think Lord Jashin would
like you guys as an offering...

200
00:15:15,393 --> 00:15:19,932
{\an1}[laugh] What's wrong?  Is
running all you can do?!

201
00:15:19,965 --> 00:15:22,837
{\an1}You're not getting away... ha!

202
00:15:22,869 --> 00:15:23,805
[chuckle]

203
00:15:28,244 --> 00:15:29,446
[spits blood]

204
00:15:35,187 --> 00:15:38,959
What? Done so soon?

205
00:15:41,129 --> 00:15:43,298
Ouch...

206
00:15:45,268 --> 00:15:46,302
Huh?

207
00:15:46,336 --> 00:15:49,474
{\an1}Seriously, that...
really hurt!

208
00:15:49,508 --> 00:15:51,411
{\an3}[gasp]

209
00:15:51,444 --> 00:15:54,348
{\an1}I'll punish you in
the name of Jashin!

210
00:16:00,322 --> 00:16:03,026
[grunt]

211
00:16:06,398 --> 00:16:08,934
Thanks, but I'm
done with this now!

212
00:16:09,436 --> 00:16:12,908
Looks like the rumors of
your immortality are true.

213
00:16:12,940 --> 00:16:16,312
{\an1}[chuckle] It's time to
start the ritual.

214
00:16:16,345 --> 00:16:18,147
[lick]

215
00:16:20,350 --> 00:16:21,186
Oh...

216
00:16:21,219 --> 00:16:23,188
{\an3}[gasp]

217
00:16:24,223 --> 00:16:27,160
{\an1}All the preparations
have been completed.

218
00:16:27,194 --> 00:16:30,833
Die!

219
00:16:33,035 --> 00:16:34,504
[gasps]

220
00:16:34,537 --> 00:16:36,974
[groan]

221
00:16:37,007 --> 00:16:39,277
{\an1}One stab through the heart

222
00:16:41,047 --> 00:16:43,217
Damn you...

223
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:47,890
{\an1}It feels so good

224
00:16:48,157 --> 00:16:51,027
{\an1}All glory be to Lord Jashin!

225
00:16:51,061 --> 00:16:56,870
[grunting]

226
00:17:00,307 --> 00:17:04,514
You bastard You
got some nerve

227
00:17:04,547 --> 00:17:06,517
{\an1}Hey!  Why didn't you die?!

228
00:17:06,550 --> 00:17:08,620
I'll beat you to death!

229
00:17:08,653 --> 00:17:10,522
But you can't!

230
00:17:10,555 --> 00:17:12,056
Did you see that?

231
00:17:12,091 --> 00:17:17,532
{\an1}Yes.  He licked Kakuzu's blood
and mentioned a ritual, probably
a jutsu...

232
00:17:18,634 --> 00:17:22,572
{\an1}Any damage he sustains affects
those whose blood he licked.

233
00:17:22,605 --> 00:17:25,877
{\an1}But that doesn't explain
his immortality...

234
00:17:25,911 --> 00:17:27,512
<i>(Konan)</i>
<i>Can you separate them?</i>

235
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:30,182
{\an1}Weren't you going
to eliminate him?

236
00:17:30,216 --> 00:17:32,620
Well...

237
00:17:33,988 --> 00:17:36,225
{\an1}<i>[crows screeching]</i>

238
00:17:36,258 --> 00:17:39,229
{\an1}Hey! What's this?!

239
00:17:41,934 --> 00:17:44,904
{\an1}What's the big idea, Itachi?!

240
00:17:44,938 --> 00:17:48,174
It seems that
we're recruiting him.

241
00:17:48,208 --> 00:17:50,645
A guy like him?

242
00:17:51,981 --> 00:17:57,589
{\an1}Are you kidding me?  No way!
Whatever this "Akatsuki" is, I
already have a mission!

243
00:17:57,622 --> 00:18:00,059
{\an1}...To spread the Way of Jashin!

244
00:18:00,091 --> 00:18:04,331
{\an1}Then you'd be wise to
join the Akatsuki... for
the sake of your mission.

245
00:18:04,364 --> 00:18:07,002
Why's that?

246
00:18:07,035 --> 00:18:10,707
{\an1}Assassination and war,
you name it...

247
00:18:10,740 --> 00:18:13,210
{\an1}...the Akatsuki are
killers for hire.

248
00:18:16,514 --> 00:18:19,285
{\an1}[metal scratching]

249
00:18:19,318 --> 00:18:25,227
{\an1}I still plan to continue
spreading the word about the Way
of Jashin, you know...

250
00:18:25,260 --> 00:18:27,697
{\an1}(Tendo Pain)
As you please.

251
00:18:30,501 --> 00:18:36,076
{\an1}Begin your missions. Our
two-man teams are in place.

252
00:18:37,544 --> 00:18:40,750
<i>(Kakuzu)</i>
<i>I didn't think I'd</i>
<i>be partnered with you.</i>

253
00:18:40,783 --> 00:18:43,987
{\an1}You took the words
right out of my mouth.

254
00:18:44,021 --> 00:18:47,026
Don't irritate me,
or I'll kill you.

255
00:18:47,059 --> 00:18:49,495
{\an1}Like I said, just try it!

256
00:18:49,528 --> 00:18:51,966
I don't want your
heart, you know.

257
00:19:06,519 --> 00:19:09,523
(Deidara)
Art is...

258
00:19:09,556 --> 00:19:12,293
[explosion]

259
00:19:12,326 --> 00:19:15,398
an explosion!

260
00:19:15,432 --> 00:19:18,803
{\an1}Huh? Yep, that's art.

261
00:19:18,836 --> 00:19:22,374
{\an1}I still don't get
what your art's about.

262
00:19:22,408 --> 00:19:27,048
{\an1}In time, you'll come to
understand the aesthetics of
something fleeting.  Hmph!

263
00:19:27,082 --> 00:19:29,151
It's our leader

264
00:19:29,185 --> 00:19:30,119
Huh?

265
00:19:32,189 --> 00:19:37,629
{\an5}<i>(Tendo Pain)</i>
<i>A shinobi village by the name of</i>
<i>the Hidden Sound was recently</i>
<i>founded. </i>

266
00:19:37,663 --> 00:19:41,434
{\an1}It's possible that Orochimaru
is involved with it.

267
00:19:41,468 --> 00:19:42,737
What?  That guy again?!

268
00:19:42,770 --> 00:19:46,274
<i>(Tendo Pain)</i>
<i>You two covertly check them out.</i>

269
00:19:46,308 --> 00:19:50,115
{\an1}Yeah, 'cause we're the best ones
at sneaking around behind the
scenes.

270
00:19:50,148 --> 00:19:52,484
Don't you worry,
I'll find him!

271
00:19:52,517 --> 00:19:54,520
He'll go boom!

272
00:19:54,553 --> 00:19:57,225
{\an1}You don't know what
"covertly" means, do you?

273
00:19:57,257 --> 00:20:01,130
<i>[waves crashing]</i>

274
00:20:01,163 --> 00:20:04,634
[thuds]

275
00:20:13,781 --> 00:20:17,253
<i>(Tendo Pain)</i>
<i>There's been an incident in</i>
<i>the Hidden Leaf Village.</i>

276
00:20:17,285 --> 00:20:21,324
{\an1}<i>Orochimaru's behind it.</i>

277
00:20:21,358 --> 00:20:27,499
{\an1}<i>Orochimaru used shinobi from the</i>
<i>Hidden Sound and Hidden Sand to</i>
<i>wage war against the Leaf, </i>

278
00:20:27,533 --> 00:20:29,703
{\an1}<i>but he failed to destroy it.</i>

279
00:20:29,737 --> 00:20:32,339
Serves him right!

280
00:20:32,373 --> 00:20:35,144
<i>(Tendo Pain)</i>
<i>The Third Hokage died, and</i>
<i>the village was damaged.</i>

281
00:20:35,178 --> 00:20:38,183
{\an1}<i>Orochimaru escaped, but</i>
<i>no one knows where.</i>

282
00:20:38,216 --> 00:20:39,818
{\an1}<i>I'll send someone to</i>
<i>investigate, but- </i>

283
00:20:39,851 --> 00:20:41,754
{\an1}I'll handle it.

284
00:20:43,756 --> 00:20:48,696
{\an5}<i>(Tendo Pain)</i>
<i>Then I'll leave this to you, as</i>
<i>well as the status of the Leaf's</i>
<i>Jinchuriki.</i>

285
00:20:48,729 --> 00:20:52,569
(Kisame)
Seems they averted total
destruction...

286
00:20:52,602 --> 00:20:56,208
{\an1}...but still sustained
massive damage.

287
00:20:56,241 --> 00:21:00,446
{\an1}The Village was at the height
of prosperity. Tragic.

288
00:21:00,479 --> 00:21:02,749
{\an1}That's not like you.

289
00:21:02,783 --> 00:21:06,622
{\an1}So even you have feelings for
your birthplace, is that it?

290
00:21:06,655 --> 00:21:08,291
{\an3}No...

291
00:21:12,797 --> 00:21:17,872
Not at all...

292
00:21:17,905 --> 00:21:21,943
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Sasuke... I hope</i>
<i>that you're safe.</i>

293
00:21:27,551 --> 00:21:37,565
♪

294
00:21:37,598 --> 00:21:47,647
♪

295
00:21:47,647 --> 00:21:57,661
♪

296
00:22:58,447 --> 00:23:01,050
<i>(Itachi)</i>
<i>It's been a long time Sasuke.</i>

297
00:23:01,083 --> 00:23:05,890
<i>(Sasuke)</i>
<i>Itachi Uchiha I hope</i>
<i>you're ready to die.</i>

298
00:23:05,923 --> 00:23:09,896
<i>(Kisame)</i>
<i>Well The Sharingan...</i>

299
00:23:09,929 --> 00:23:12,433
{\an1}<i>...And he looks an</i>
<i>awful lot like you...</i>

300
00:23:12,466 --> 00:23:14,469
{\an1}<i>...Itachi, who is this kid?</i>

301
00:23:14,503 --> 00:23:16,605
<i>(Itachi)</i>
<i>He's my younger brother.</i>

302
00:23:16,638 --> 00:23:21,913
<i>(Itachi)</i>
<i>Next time on Naruto</i>
<i>Shippuden: "Truth."</i>

303
00:23:21,946 --> 00:23:24,617
<i>(Itachi)</i>
<i>So you've awakened your</i>
<i>Sharingan...</i>

304
00:23:28,189 --> 00:23:35,399
♪

